org.wiigee.event
Class InfraredEvent

java.lang.Object
  java.util.EventObject
      org.wiigee.event.InfraredEvent
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class InfraredEvent
extends java.util.EventObject

Defines the IR events. An infrared event consists of a set of coordinates, containing values from [0, 1024] in width to [0, 768] in height. for each point there is a given size and if the detected infrared spot is valid.

Author:
Benjamin 'BePo' Poppinga, upgraded by Santiago Hors Fraile

coordinates

size

protected int[] size

valid

protected boolean[] valid
Each cell represents if the IR spot is valid or not. It is valid if the spot coordinates are between 0 and 1023 for x and y.
